[30;1m27 | [0m[35m    The idea is that a vector instance stores a representation in Cartesian,[0m
[30;1m28 | [0m[35m    spherical and cylindrical coordinates. All arguments are optional, however[0m
[30;1m29 | [0m[35m    the user needs to provide one of the combinations of either (x, y, z) values[0m
